properties.name: Big Ben
properties.description: Posted by TgencayAbingdon Street London SW1P 3JY United KingdomBig Ben can be see from almost anywhere in London. Until I went to London, I was unaware that the actual tower is not named \'Big Ben\' but \'Big Ben\' is the name of the bell inside the tower.

properties.name: Buckingham Palace
properties.description: Posted by TgencayLondonQueen Elisabeth II and her family reside in this fabulous palace. It was constantly guarded by guards who would not crack a smile no matter how hard you tried to make them.

properties.name: Hard Rock Cafe
properties.description: Posted by Tgencay 150 Old Park Lane London W1K1QZ, EnglandThis Hard Rock Cafe in London started it all. I was so excited because I got to order my first drink all by myself here!

properties.name: Harrod
properties.description: Posted by TgencayHarrods (the world\'s largest department store) lives up to its name. You are able to find anything and everything there from a washing machine to a bagle to makeup. Although things are a little pricy it was for sure worth the trip over there.

properties.name: Houses of Parliament
properties.description: Posted by TgencayLondon SW1A 0AA

properties.name: Kensington Palace
properties.description: Posted by TgencayLondon W8 4PXThis palace was the former residence of Queen Victoria as well as Princess Diana. The estate surrounded my beautiful gardens as far as the eyes can see. Inside the palace you can see the beautiful dresses that Princes Diana wore.

properties.name: McGhee Tyson Airport
properties.description: Posted by Tgencay2055 Alcoa Highway, Alcoa TNWe took off from McGhee Tyson airport and the crack of dawn in an airplane that seriously was about the size of a pack of gum!

properties.name: Primeminister's Residence
properties.description: Posted by Tgencay10 Downing Street10 Downing Street is the residence of England\'s prime minister and his family. This place was heavily guarded by gates and guards at all times.

properties.name: Prince Edward Theatre
properties.description: Posted by Tgencay 28 Old Compton Street London, W1D 4HSMy mom and I saw Mary Poppins at the Prince Edward Theatre. Not only was the interior of the theatre absolutely beautiful but the play was wonderful.

properties.name: Spencer House
properties.description: Posted by Tgencay27 St James\'s Place, London SW1A 1NRThis house was occupied by the Spencer family (the Late Princess Diana\'s ancestors) as well as tenants who they rented it out to. The house has been restored and now can be toured by the public.

properties.name: Tower of London
properties.description: Posted by TgencayTower Hill, London EC3N 4ABWhat I thought was only a tower when I first came to England was actually a fortress. This place houses the gorgeous crown jewels.

properties.name: Victoria Park Plaza
properties.description: Posted by Tgencay23p Vauxhall Bridge Road, London SW1V 1EQ, United KingdomMy mom and I stayed in the beautiful Victoria Park Plaza which was just a quick walk to Buckingham Palace.

properties.name: Westminster Abbey
properties.description: Posted by Tgencay20 Dean\'s Yard London, EnglandSW1P 3PAWestminster Abbey was so beautiful that words can no do it justice. The incredible windows and the carvings in the walls were simply amazing. However I did feel a little weird that there were dead bodies just laying all around me.
